# ============================================================
# OceanWatch AI — Environment Configuration Example
# ============================================================
# Copy this file to .env (or just set these in your browser)
# NOTE: API keys are stored in browser localStorage, NOT in code.
# This file is for documentation purposes only.
# ============================================================

# Google Gemini API Key (FREE — no credit card needed)
# Get yours at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# This key powers the AI chat assistant with natural language responses.
# Without it, the chat falls back to basic keyword matching (still works!).
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ============================================================
# HOW TO SET YOUR API KEY:
# ============================================================
# Option 1 (Recommended): Open the dashboard → Type "settings" in the
#   AI chat → Paste your key → Click "Save Key"
#
# Option 2 (Manual): Open browser DevTools (F12) → Console → Run:
#   localStorage.setItem('oceanwatch_gemini_key', 'YOUR_KEY_HERE')
#
# The key is stored ONLY in your browser's localStorage.
# It is NEVER saved in any source code file.
# It is NEVER sent anywhere except Google's Gemini API.
# ============================================================

# ============================================================
# OCEAN DATA APIs (NO KEY NEEDED — completely free)
# ============================================================
# These are used automatically. No configuration needed.
# - Open-Meteo Weather API: https://api.open-meteo.com
# - Open-Meteo Marine API: https://marine-api.open-meteo.com
